{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1778095776,"nonce":"o35mV7Uil175Wkx/CAmmgyjJL0k=","title":"Project analyses coordination","message":"Central coordination umbrella for project-wide decisions about analyses. Comments here capture **cross-cutting opinions** — individual analysis issues focus on the analysis itself; how analyses fit into the bigger scheme is dealt with HERE.\n\n## What goes on this umbrella (NOT on individual analysis issues)\n\n- **New analyses worth doing.** File a normal issue for the analysis, AND comment here with: new issue ID, initial tier guess (essential / desirable / auxiliary), one-line rationale.\n- **Tier shifts** (essential ↔ desirable ↔ auxiliary ↔ deprecated). Issue ID(s), old tier → new tier, reason.\n- **Cross-cutting findings** affecting multiple analyses (e.g. \"X turned out subsumed by Y\", \"Z became less informative after we changed training method\").\n- **Deprecation / archival** of analyses no longer pursued.\n\n## What goes on individual analysis issues\n\nThe analysis itself: design, math, implementation, tests, results, scope.\n\n## Initial tier ordering (2026-05-06, derived from synthesis_review.md §8 cross-walk)\n\n**Essential** — currently on the critical path for the methodology-fix phase (b557d4e):\n- `17137e6` — Steady-state FPs + Jacobian eigendecomposition (synthesis-4 Prediction 2 alignment)\n- `c500097` — Input-Jacobian SVD across SISU\n- `89891ab` — Adversary strategy verification + Helmholtz decomposition\n- `74bfd86` — Induced-gain ||T_{w-\u003ez}||_inf analyser\n- `a5e1450` — Cross-partial ∇²_{θδ}L diagnostic\n\n**Desirable**:\n- `bde625b` — PCA + tangling\n- `753508c` — Formal BCS/DAI/PAI-ASF analysis\n- `84ee4ff` — APT/CVaR worst-case methods\n- `5efa4ca` — Frequency response\n\n**Auxiliary / lower priority**:\n- `ce34c2c` — GRU laziness investigation (architecture sweep gave 0% Δv across vRNN/GRU × additive/multiplicative)\n\n(Other Part 1 / Part 2 analysis issues from `297260c` and `0af472c` are unranked here pending review; will be added via comments as they are (re)considered.)\n\n## Protocol\n\n- **Do NOT reference this umbrella in commit `Bug:` trailers** — that auto-closes the umbrella on merge (the same accident that closed `b557d4e`). Reference only the relevant child issues.\n- Comments are timestamped + threaded so the trail of cross-cutting decisions is recoverable.\n\n## Scope\n\nProject-lifetime, cross-phase. Distinct from phase umbrellas like:\n- `b557d4e` — methodology-fix phase (synthesis-review-driven)\n- `297260c` — Part 1 analysis modules (subset umbrella)\n- `0af472c` — Part 2 analysis modules (subset umbrella)\n\nFuture phase umbrellas should be added as comments here when instantiated, so this issue serves as a discovery surface for \"what umbrellas are active right now.\"","files":null}]}